<p>Follow up <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/q/32924510/206466">to this question</a></p>  <p>I had tried this configuration and set a breakpoint, but the method never gets called</p>  <pre><code>@Configuration class MyConfig {    @Autowired void configureObjectMapper( ObjectMapper mapper ) { ...} } </code></pre>  <p>This however does work</p>  <pre><code>@Required @Autowired private void configureObjectMapper( final ObjectMapper objectMapper) {     objectMapper.disable( SerializationFeature.WRITE_DATES_AS_TIMESTAMPS ); } </code></pre>  <p>I also tried this, but it blows up with not having a noargs constructor (you can do this with services/controllers/components now, so why doesn't it work here?)</p>  <pre><code>@Configuration class MyConfig {      @Autowired     MyConfig( final ObjectMapper mapper ) {        ...     } } </code></pre>  <p>and yet this works</p>  <pre><code>@Configuration // or @Service or some bean class SomeClass ... {      @Autowired     private ObjectMapper objectMapper;      @PostConstruct     private void configureObjectMapper() {         objectMapper.disable( SerializationFeature.WRITE_DATES_AS_TIMESTAMPS );     }  } </code></pre>  <p>why isn't <code>@Configuration</code> working like other spring managed classes?</p>